  "texts": [
    "What we can expect is, at best, some \"good enough\" ones.",
    "Objective and overview of this manuscriptIn this work we present the thesis that while AI has advanced significantly the latest years compared to the last few decades, it is fundamentally different from NI, and it currently lacks the capacity to accurately replicate the complexities of basic human characteristics like cognition and agency.",
    "The paper meticulously explores the divergences between AI and NI, tries to assess the limitations of current AI technologies, and explores the ethical and societal implications of these developments.",
    "Key findings and conclusions1.",
    "Distinct Constructs: AI and NI are essentially different constructs, with AI presenting an imitation of certain cognitive functions rather than a true replication of human intelligence."
